      "handlerPdf": "PDF document operations (generate/read/modify/convert/analyze)",
      "faqQ0": "How to configure LLM provider?",
      "faqA0": "In Settings > LLM Configuration, click the \"Add Provider\" button, select the provider type (OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini/Ollama/Custom), and fill in the API URL, API Key, and model name.",
      "faqQ1": "What document formats are supported?",
      "faqA1": "Supports Word(.docx), Excel(.xlsx), PowerPoint(.pptx), PDF(.pdf) and Markdown(.md) format generation, reading and modification, as well as mutual conversion between these formats.",
      "faqQ2": "How to create a custom Handler?",
      "faqA2": "In Settings > Handlers Management, click the \"Add Custom Handler\" button. Custom Handlers are essentially Prompt templates that support {{param_name}} placeholders, which are automatically replaced when Agent calls them.",
      "faqQ3": "How does Agent confirm high-risk operations?",
      "faqA3": "When Agent performs high-risk operations such as deletion or overwriting, a confirmation dialog will pop up, and you can choose to approve or reject. The confirmation level can be adjusted in Settings > General (Always confirm / Confirm edits only / Auto-confirm all).",
      "faqQ4": "How to view document version history?",
      "faqA4": "Right-click a file in the file tree and select \"Version History\", or click the version history button in the document preview panel. A version snapshot is automatically created before each document modification, and you can roll back to any historical version.",
      "faqQ5": "How to switch workspaces?",
      "faqA5": "Click the workspace selector in the top bar to switch workspaces, or add, switch and manage workspaces in Settings > Workspace Management. Each workspace's files and configuration are independent.",
      "faqQ6": "How to use Prompt templates?",
      "faqA6": "You can create and manage commonly used Prompt templates in Settings > Prompt Templates, with support for variable placeholders. You can quickly insert template content through the template picker in the input box."
    }
  },
